definitions.definition: A number of villages and hamlets in England :

subdefinitions.definition: A village and civil parish in East Cambridgeshire district, Cambridgeshire ( OS grid ref TL6961 ) .
A village and civil parish in Cheshire East district, Cheshire ( OS grid ref SJ7784 ) .
A settlement in St Leonards and St Ives parish, east Dorset ( OS grid ref SU1304 ) .
A village and civil parish (without a council) in Cotswold district, Gloucestershire ( OS grid ref ST9394 ) .
A hamlet in Bentworth parish, East Hampshire district, Hampshire ( OS grid ref SU6440 ) .
A suburb in New Milton parish, New Forest district, Hampshire ( OS grid ref SZ2595 ) .
A village and civil parish (without a council) in Test Valley district, Hampshire . ( OS grid ref SU3831 ) .
A hamlet in Sutton parish, Dover district, Kent ( OS grid ref TR3048 ) .
A village and civil parish in North Northamptonshire district, Northamptonshire , previously in Kettering district ( OS grid ref SP7990 ) .
A village in Loggerheads parish, Newcastle-under-Lyme district, Staffordshire ( OS grid ref SJ7636 ) .
A village in Box parish, Wiltshire ( OS grid ref ST8168 ) .

definitions.definition: A surname from Old English derived from the places in England.
A male given name transferred from the surname .
A female given name transferred from the surname .
A number of places in the United States :

subdefinitions.definition: A minor city in Washington County , Illinois ; named for railroad official Col. L. W. Ashley.
A town in Smithfield Township, DeKalb County and Steuben Township, Steuben County , Indiana .
A village in Elba Township, Gratiot County , Michigan .
A census-designated place in Pike County , Missouri ; named for the state's first lieutenant governor, William Henry Ashley .
A city , the county seat of McIntosh County , North Dakota ; named for railroad official Ashley E. Morrow.
A village in Oxford Township, Delaware County , Ohio ; named for Col. L. W. Ashley.
A borough in Luzerne County , Pennsylvania .
An unincorporated community in Doddridge County , West Virginia ; named for the local Ash family.
An unincorporated community in the towns of Guenther and Knowlton , Marathon County , Wisconsin .

definitions.definition: A locality in Moree Plains Shire, New South Wales , Australia ; named for one of the settlements in England.
A small settlement and river north of Rangiora , Canterbury , New Zealand .
